---
title: Hoisin Sriracha Pork & Pineapple Stir-Fry with Long Green Pepper over Sesame Scallion Black Rice
description: Falling into a stir-fry rut with the same meat, veggie, and sauce combo each week? We’ve got you covered. This version stars ground pork, which we brown with long green pepper and pineapple, then coat in a delectably sweet, savory, and spicy hoisin and sriracha sauce. It’s all served over nutty black rice studded with sesame seeds and scallion greens, then drizzled with more sriracha for customizable heat. Dinner winner? We think so.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/hoisin-sriracha-pork-pineapple-stir-fry-c2ed1681.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/hoisin-sriracha-pork-pineapple-stir-fry-6022ac15179b5a4089026432-708a3511.pdf
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 830 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 410 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/hoisin-sriracha-pork-and-pineapple-stir-fry-6022ac15179b5a4089026432
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1%unit}.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens.

Meanwhile, drain @pineapple{4%oz} over a #small bowl{}, reserving juice.

To #bowl{} with juice, whisk in @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}, @cornstarch{1%tbsp}, @sriracha{1%tsp}, and @water{2%tbsp}.

> Save the rest of the sriracha for serving if desired.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%oz} and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Push pork to one side of pan; add another drizzle of oil and green pepper to empty side. Cook, stirring, until green pepper is lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add scallion whites and pineapple to side of pan with green pepper; season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until scallion whites are slightly softened and pineapple is lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Pour hoisin sriracha mixture into pan with stir-fry; stir everything together until pork is cooked through and stir-fry is thoroughly combined and coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Add a splash of water if sauce is too thick.

Turn off heat. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Massage @microwavable black rice{1%unit} in package to break up grains. Partially open top of package. Microwave for ~{90%seconds}, then carefully transfer rice to a #medium bowl{}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, scallion greens, and @sesame seeds{1/2%tbsp}. Fluff with a #fork{} and season with @salt{pinch}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with stir-fry. Drizzle with remaining @?sriracha{} if desired and sprinkle with remaining sesame seeds as you like. Serve.